The Walking Dead: Season Two - the continuation of the first season 
of The Walking Dead. This is an episodic video game on the principle 
of point-and-click adventure genre system based on the comic book 
by Robert Kirkman, "The Walking Dead." The game is developed by studio 
Telltale Games. The second season of the game continues the story of 
Clementine, orphans of Atlanta, left to fend for themselves to survive 
in a world that has gone mad. Developers explained that the action 
of the first episode begins in the same place where ended the fifth 
episode of the first season. Season 2 will also use conservation adopted 
five players and a further sixth episode. In season 2, players will play 
for Clementine.
